{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.5",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 5 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:1",
      "text": "But Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:2",
      "text": "For wrath destroys the foolish one, and envy slays him that has gone astray.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:3",
      "text": "And I have seen foolish ones taking root: but suddenly their habitation was devoured.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:4",
      "text": "Let their children be far from safety, and let them be crushed at the doors of vile men, and let there be no deliverer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:5",
      "text": "For what they have collected, the just shall eat; but they shall not be delivered out of calamities: let their strength be utterly exhausted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:6",
      "text": "For labour cannot by any means come out of the earth, nor shall trouble spring out of the mountains:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:7",
      "text": "yet man is born to labour, and even so the vulture's young seek the high places.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:8",
      "text": "Nevertheless I will beseech the Lord, and will call upon the Lord, the sovereign of all;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:9",
      "text": "who does great things and untraceable, glorious things also, and marvellous, of which there is no number:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:10",
      "text": "who gives rain upon the earth, sending water on the earth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:11",
      "text": "who exalts the lowly, and raises up them that are lost:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:12",
      "text": "frustrating the counsels of the crafty, and their hands shall not perform the truth:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:13",
      "text": "who takes the wise in their wisdom, and subverts the counsel of the crafty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:14",
      "text": "In the day darkness shall come upon them, and let them grope in the noon-day even as in the night:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:15",
      "text": "and let them perish in war, and let the weak escape from the hand of the mighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:16",
      "text": "And let the weak have hope, but the mouth of the unjust be stopped.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:17",
      "text": "But blessed is the man whom the Lord has reproved; and reject not thou the chastening of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:18",
      "text": "For he causes a man to be in pain, and restores him again: he smites, and his hands heal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:19",
      "text": "Six times he shall deliver thee out of distresses: and in the seventh harm shall not touch thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:20",
      "text": "In famine he shall deliver thee from death: and in war he shall free thee from the power of the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:21",
      "text": "He shall hide thee from the scourge of the tongue: and thou shalt not be afraid of coming evils.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:22",
      "text": "Thou shalt laugh at the unrighteous and the lawless: and thou shalt not be afraid of wild beasts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:23",
      "text": "For the wild beasts of the field shall be at peace with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:24",
      "text": "Then shalt thou know that thy house shall be at peace, and the provision for thy tabernacle shall not fail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:25",
      "text": "And thou shalt know that thy seed shall be abundant; and thy children shall be like the herbage of the field.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:26",
      "text": "And thou shalt come to the grave like ripe corn reaped in its season, or as a heap of the corn-flour collected in proper time.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.5.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 5:27",
      "text": "Behold, we have thus sought out these matters; these are what we have heard: but do thou reflect with thyself, if thou hast done anything wrong.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
